Package: FuncSlide
Title: Sliding Window Functions for Time Series Analysis
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Zin Min", "Thet Lwin", email = "zinmin20@gmail.com", role = c("aut"))
Description: Provides tools for processing and analyzing multidimensional
    time series data using sliding window techniques. The package includes
    functions to import data from CSV files, compute a combined acceleration
    vector using the Euclidean norm, and apply customizable window-based
    functions such as mean smoothing, binary classification, and threshold
    filtering. It also offers visualization tools to compare raw and processed
    signals using ggplot2.
